cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IT 

This paper deals with privacy protection mechanisms for user data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the impact of these mechanisms on the trade-off between privacy protection and user utility, which involves data management and machine learning techniques (cs.DB, cs.LG). The paper also derives theoretical bounds on privacy protection, which involves information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the use of statistical matching techniques, which involves data mining and machine learning (cs.SI).
